Leah Bracknell https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leah_Bracknell 0 Alison Rosalind Bracknell (born 12 July 1964), known professionally as Leah Bracknell, is an English actress, known for her role as Zoe Tate in the ITV soap opera Emmerdale (1989—2005), for which she was nominated for the 2002 National Television Award for Most Popular Actress and won the 2006 British Soap Award for Best Exit. She is also a qualified teacher with the British School of Yoga and designs and produces her own line of jewellery.
